cs.CL, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.DS 

The paper discusses probabilistic topic models, which are commonly used in natural language processing (NLP) and information retrieval (IR) tasks. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also proposes a novel measure for evaluating topic quality, which involves Bayesian inference methods such as Gibbs sampling, indicating a connection to cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of multiple metrics for topic quality estimation, which suggests a connection to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
